The paper proposes a new protocol for debugging concurrent software systems that decouples the debugger from the specific concurrency models employed by the target application. This is a software engineering problem that involves programming languages (cs.PL), software engineering (cs.SE), distributed computing (cs.DC), deep learning (cs.DL), and machine learning (cs.LG) since the authors use machine learning techniques to visualize concurrent interactions. However, since the paper focuses on programming languages and software engineering, cs.PL and cs.SE are the most likely categories.
